This paper deals with text classification tasks and machine teaching techniques, which are commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) communities. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses ensemble learning techniques, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for identifying sparsely distributed examples from large volumes of unlabeled data, which is related to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of labeling functions, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) tasks, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the augmentation of data sets, which is a common technique in data science (DS), making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category as well.
